{
  "video_id": "8T_jwq9ph8k",
  "title": "Why people believe weird things | Michael Shermer",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 25000.0,
      "end_time": 27532.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m Michael Shermer, director of the Skeptics Society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 27556.0,
      "end_time": 29880.0,
      "text": "publisher of \"Skeptic\" magazine."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 29112.0,
      "end_time": 31250.0,
      "text": "We investigate claims of the paranormal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 31490.0,
      "end_time": 34731.0,
      "text": "pseudo-science, fringe groups and cults, and claims of all kinds between,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 34755.0,
      "end_time": 37649.0,
      "text": "science and pseudo-science and non-science and junk science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 37673.0,
      "end_time": 40976.0,
      "text": "voodoo science, pathological science, bad science, non-science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 41000.0,
      "end_time": 42887.0,
      "text": "and plain old non-sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 42911.0,
      "end_time": 44828.0,
      "text": "And unless you&#39;ve been on Mars recently,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 44852.0,
      "end_time": 46870.0,
      "text": "you know there&#39;s a lot of that out there."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 46894.0,
      "end_time": 49916.0,
      "text": "Some people call us debunkers, which is kind of a negative term."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 49940.0,
      "end_time": 52470.0,
      "text": "But let&#39;s face it, there&#39;s a lot of bunk."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 52720.0,
      "end_time": 55525.0,
      "text": "We are like the bunko squads of the police departments out there --"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 55549.0,
      "end_time": 58976.0,
      "text": "well, we&#39;re sort of like the Ralph Naders of bad ideas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 59000.0,
      "end_time": 60230.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 60254.0,
      "end_time": 62976.0,
      "text": "trying to replace bad ideas with good ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 63000.0,
      "end_time": 64863.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll show you an example of a bad idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64887.0,
      "end_time": 66450.0,
      "text": "I brought this with me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 66690.0,
      "end_time": 69976.0,
      "text": "this was given to us by NBC Dateline to test."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 70000.0,
      "end_time": 73286.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s produced by the Quadro Corporation of West Virginia."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 73310.0,
      "end_time": 76220.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s called the Quadro 2000 Dowser Rod."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 76244.0,
      "end_time": 77690.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 77714.0,
      "end_time": 82976.0,
      "text": "This was being sold to high-school administrators for $900 apiece."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 83000.0,
      "end_time": 87327.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a piece of plastic with a Radio Shack antenna attached to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 87351.0,
      "end_time": 89317.0,
      "text": "You could dowse for all sorts of things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89341.0,
      "end_time": 92734.0,
      "text": "but this particular one was built to dowse for marijuana"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92758.0,
      "end_time": 93976.0,
      "text": "in students&#39; lockers."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 94000.0,
      "end_time": 96460.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96484.0,
      "end_time": 100290.0,
      "text": "So the way it works is you go down the hallway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 100530.0,
      "end_time": 103510.0,
      "text": "and you see if it tilts toward a particular locker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103760.0,
      "end_time": 104520.0,
      "text": "and then you open the locker."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 104544.0,
      "end_time": 106121.0,
      "text": "So it looks something like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 106145.0,
      "end_time": 107328.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll show you."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 108809.0,
      "end_time": 109976.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110000.0,
      "end_time": 113391.0,
      "text": "Well, it has kind of a right-leaning bias."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113415.0,
      "end_time": 116220.0,
      "text": "Well, this is science, so we&#39;ll do a controlled experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 116244.0,
      "end_time": 117826.0,
      "text": "It&#39;ll go this way for sure."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 117850.0,
      "end_time": 121783.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 121808.0,
      "end_time": 124334.0,
      "text": "Sir, do you want to empty your pockets, please, sir?"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 124358.0,
      "end_time": 126196.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 126220.0,
      "end_time": 129676.0,
      "text": "So the question was, can it actually find marijuana in students&#39; lockers?"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129701.0,
      "end_time": 132299.0,
      "text": "And the answer is, if you open enough of them, yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132323.0,
      "end_time": 133346.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133370.0,
      "end_time": 134976.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 135000.0,
      "end_time": 138381.0,
      "text": "But in science, we have to keep track of the misses, not just the hits."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 138405.0,
      "end_time": 141671.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s probably the key lesson to my short talk here:"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 141695.0,
      "end_time": 145429.0,
      "text": "This is how psychics work, astrologers, tarot card readers and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 145453.0,
      "end_time": 147672.0,
      "text": "People remember the hits and forget the misses."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 147696.0,
      "end_time": 149591.0,
      "text": "In science, we keep the whole database,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 149615.0,
      "end_time": 152276.0,
      "text": "and look to see if the number of hits somehow stands out"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 152300.0,
      "end_time": 154513.0,
      "text": "from the total number you&#39;d expect by chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 154537.0,
      "end_time": 155831.0,
      "text": "In this case, we tested it."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 155855.0,
      "end_time": 157346.0,
      "text": "We had two opaque boxes:"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 157371.0,
      "end_time": 161500.0,
      "text": "one with government-approved THC marijuana, and one with nothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 161290.0,
      "end_time": 162910.0,
      "text": "And it got it 50 percent of the time --"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 162934.0,
      "end_time": 164270.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 164510.0,
      "end_time": 166976.0,
      "text": "which is exactly what you&#39;d expect with a coin-flip model."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 167000.0,
      "end_time": 170991.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s just a fun little example here of the sorts of things we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 171150.0,
      "end_time": 174482.0,
      "text": "\"Skeptic\" is the quarterly publication. Each one has a particular theme."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 174507.0,
      "end_time": 176581.0,
      "text": "This one is on the future of intelligence."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 176605.0,
      "end_time": 178375.0,
      "text": "Are people getting smarter or dumber?"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 178400.0,
      "end_time": 181448.0,
      "text": "I have an opinion of this myself because of the business I&#39;m in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 181472.0,
      "end_time": 184139.0,
      "text": "but in fact, people, it turns out, are getting smarter."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 184163.0,
      "end_time": 186976.0,
      "text": "Three IQ points per 10 years, going up."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 187000.0,
      "end_time": 188651.0,
      "text": "Sort of an interesting thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 188675.0,
      "end_time": 192222.0,
      "text": "With science, don&#39;t think of skepticism as a thing, or science as a thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 192246.0,
      "end_time": 193976.0,
      "text": "Are science and religion compatible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 194000.0,
      "end_time": 196231.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s like, are science and plumbing compatible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 196255.0,
      "end_time": 197888.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re just two different things."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 197913.0,
      "end_time": 199652.0,
      "text": "Science is not a thing. It&#39;s a verb."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 199676.0,
      "end_time": 201398.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a way of thinking about things."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 201422.0,
      "end_time": 204492.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a way of looking for natural explanations for all phenomena."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 204516.0,
      "end_time": 205866.0,
      "text": "I mean, what&#39;s more likely:"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 205890.0,
      "end_time": 209452.0,
      "text": "that extraterrestrial intelligences or multi-dimensional beings"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 209477.0,
      "end_time": 211867.0,
      "text": "travel across vast distances of interstellar space"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 211891.0,
      "end_time": 215710.0,
      "text": "to leave a crop circle in Farmer Bob&#39;s field in Puckerbrush, Kansas"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 215950.0,
      "end_time": 216905.0,
      "text": "to promote skeptic.com, our web page?"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 216929.0,
      "end_time": 221407.0,
      "text": "Or is it more likely that a reader of \"Skeptic\" did this with Photoshop?"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 221431.0,
      "end_time": 223810.0,
      "text": "And in all cases we have to ask --"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 223105.0,
      "end_time": 224929.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 224953.0,
      "end_time": 226976.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s the more likely explanation?"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 227000.0,
      "end_time": 229167.0,
      "text": "Before we say something is out of this world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 229191.0,
      "end_time": 231855.0,
      "text": "we should first make sure that it&#39;s not in this world."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 231879.0,
      "end_time": 233300.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s more likely:"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 233540.0,
      "end_time": 236380.0,
      "text": "that Arnold had extraterrestrial help in his run for the governorship,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 236404.0,
      "end_time": 238902.0,
      "text": "or that the \"World Weekly News\" makes stuff up?"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 238926.0,
      "end_time": 240315.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 240339.0,
      "end_time": 245100.0,
      "text": "The same theme is expressed nicely here in this Sidney Harris cartoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 245250.0,
      "end_time": 248240.0,
      "text": "For those of you in the back, it says here: \"Then a miracle occurs."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 248264.0,
      "end_time": 250976.0,
      "text": "I think you need to be more explicit here in step two.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 251000.0,
      "end_time": 255496.0,
      "text": "This single slide completely dismantles the intelligent design arguments."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 255520.0,
      "end_time": 257368.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s nothing more to it than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 257392.0,
      "end_time": 258442.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 258466.0,
      "end_time": 259853.0,
      "text": "You can say a miracle occurs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 259878.0,
      "end_time": 262844.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s just that it doesn&#39;t explain anything or offer anything."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 262868.0,
      "end_time": 264180.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s nothing to test."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 264420.0,
      "end_time": 267489.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the end of the conversation for intelligent design creationists."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 267514.0,
      "end_time": 272400.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s true, scientists sometimes throw terms out as linguistic place fillers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 272424.0,
      "end_time": 274772.0,
      "text": "dark energy or dark matter, something like that --"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 274796.0,
      "end_time": 277256.0,
      "text": "until we figure out what it is, we&#39;ll call it this."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 277280.0,
      "end_time": 279981.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the beginning of the causal chain for science."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 280500.0,
      "end_time": 284800.0,
      "text": "For intelligent design creationists, it&#39;s the end of the chain."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 284104.0,
      "end_time": 286276.0,
      "text": "So again, we can ask this: what&#39;s more likely?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 286300.0,
      "end_time": 290691.0,
      "text": "Are UFOs alien spaceships, or perceptual cognitive mistakes, or even fakes?"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 290715.0,
      "end_time": 293976.0,
      "text": "This is a UFO shot from my house in Altadena, California,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 294000.0,
      "end_time": 295976.0,
      "text": "looking down over Pasadena."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 296000.0,
      "end_time": 299521.0,
      "text": "And if it looks a lot like a Buick hubcap, it&#39;s because it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 299545.0,
      "end_time": 302283.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t even need Photoshop or high-tech equipment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 302307.0,
      "end_time": 303505.0,
      "text": "you don&#39;t need computers."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 303529.0,
      "end_time": 306976.0,
      "text": "This was shot with a throwaway Kodak Instamatic camera."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 307000.0,
      "end_time": 310960.0,
      "text": "You just have somebody off on the side with a hubcap ready to go."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 310120.0,
      "end_time": 312180.0,
      "text": "Camera&#39;s ready -- that&#39;s it."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 312420.0,
      "end_time": 313479.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 313503.0,
      "end_time": 316976.0,
      "text": "So, although it&#39;s possible that most of these things are fake"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 317000.0,
      "end_time": 320714.0,
      "text": "or illusions or so on, and that some of them are real,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 320738.0,
      "end_time": 323871.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s more likely that all of them are fake, like the crop circles."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 323895.0,
      "end_time": 327275.0,
      "text": "On a more serious note, in all of science we&#39;re looking for a balance"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 327300.0,
      "end_time": 328976.0,
      "text": "between data and theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 329000.0,
      "end_time": 332976.0,
      "text": "In the case of Galileo, he had two problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 333000.0,
      "end_time": 335361.0,
      "text": "when he turned his telescope to Saturn."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 335385.0,
      "end_time": 338507.0,
      "text": "First of all, there was no theory of planetary rings."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 338531.0,
      "end_time": 340724.0,
      "text": "Second of all, his data was grainy and fuzzy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 340748.0,
      "end_time": 343276.0,
      "text": "and he couldn&#39;t quite make out what he was looking at."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 343300.0,
      "end_time": 344976.0,
      "text": "So he wrote that he had seen --"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 345000.0,
      "end_time": 348507.0,
      "text": "\"I have observed that the furthest planet has three bodies.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 348531.0,
      "end_time": 351396.0,
      "text": "And this is what he ended up concluding that he saw."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 351420.0,
      "end_time": 354976.0,
      "text": "So without a theory of planetary rings and with only grainy data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 355000.0,
      "end_time": 356918.0,
      "text": "you can&#39;t have a good theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 356942.0,
      "end_time": 358561.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t solved until 1655."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 358585.0,
      "end_time": 361599.0,
      "text": "This is Christiaan Huygens&#39;s book that catalogs all the mistakes"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 361623.0,
      "end_time": 364585.0,
      "text": "people made trying to figure out what was going on with Saturn."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 364609.0,
      "end_time": 366465.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t till Huygens had two things:"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 366489.0,
      "end_time": 370974.0,
      "text": "He had a good theory of planetary rings and how the solar system operated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 370999.0,
      "end_time": 373862.0,
      "text": "and he had better telescopic, more fine-grain data"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 373886.0,
      "end_time": 377429.0,
      "text": "in which he could figure out that as the Earth is going around faster --"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 377453.0,
      "end_time": 380681.0,
      "text": "according to Kepler&#39;s Laws -- than Saturn, then we catch up with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 380705.0,
      "end_time": 383976.0,
      "text": "And we see the angles of the rings at different angles, there."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 384000.0,
      "end_time": 386220.0,
      "text": "And that, in fact, turns out to be true."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 386244.0,
      "end_time": 391541.0,
      "text": "The problem with having a theory is that it may be loaded with cognitive biases."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 391565.0,
      "end_time": 394832.0,
      "text": "So one of the problems of explaining why people believe weird things"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 394856.0,
      "end_time": 396924.0,
      "text": "is that we have things, on a simple level,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 396948.0,
      "end_time": 398775.0,
      "text": "and then I&#39;ll go to more serious ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 398800.0,
      "end_time": 400676.0,
      "text": "Like, we have a tendency to see faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 400700.0,
      "end_time": 402476.0,
      "text": "This is the face on Mars."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 402500.0,
      "end_time": 407120.0,
      "text": "In 1976, where there was a whole movement to get NASA to photograph that area"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 407360.0,
      "end_time": 410952.0,
      "text": "because people thought this was monumental architecture made by Martians."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 410976.0,
      "end_time": 413747.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the close-up of it from 2001."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 413771.0,
      "end_time": 416231.0,
      "text": "If you squint, you can still see the face."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 416255.0,
      "end_time": 417557.0,
      "text": "And when you&#39;re squinting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 417581.0,
      "end_time": 420604.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re turning that from fine-grain to coarse-grain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 420628.0,
      "end_time": 422914.0,
      "text": "so you&#39;re reducing the quality of your data."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 422939.0,
      "end_time": 426168.0,
      "text": "And if I didn&#39;t tell you what to look for, you&#39;d still see the face,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 426192.0,
      "end_time": 428621.0,
      "text": "because we&#39;re programmed by evolution to see faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 428645.0,
      "end_time": 430796.0,
      "text": "Faces are important for us socially."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 430820.0,
      "end_time": 434288.0,
      "text": "And of course, happy faces, faces of all kinds are easy to see."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 434312.0,
      "end_time": 436208.0,
      "text": "You see the happy face on Mars, there."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 436232.0,
      "end_time": 437383.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 437407.0,
      "end_time": 440320.0,
      "text": "If astronomers were frogs, perhaps they&#39;d see Kermit the Frog."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 440344.0,
      "end_time": 442296.0,
      "text": "Do you see him there? Little froggy legs."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 442688.0,
      "end_time": 444883.0,
      "text": "Or if geologists were elephants?"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 445736.0,
      "end_time": 448976.0,
      "text": "Religious iconography."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 449000.0,
      "end_time": 451801.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 451825.0,
      "end_time": 453976.0,
      "text": "Discovered by a Tennessee baker in 1996."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 454000.0,
      "end_time": 456477.0,
      "text": "He charged five bucks a head to come see the nun bun"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 456501.0,
      "end_time": 460214.0,
      "text": "till he got a cease-and-desist from Mother Teresa&#39;s lawyer."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 460238.0,
      "end_time": 463976.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s Our Lady of Guadalupe and Our Lady of Watsonville, just down the street,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 464000.0,
      "end_time": 465604.0,
      "text": "or is it up the street from here?"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 465628.0,
      "end_time": 468976.0,
      "text": "Tree bark is particularly good because it&#39;s nice and grainy, branchy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 469000.0,
      "end_time": 472000.0,
      "text": "black-and-white splotchy and you can get the pattern-seeking --"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 472240.0,
      "end_time": 473976.0,
      "text": "humans are pattern-seeking animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 474000.0,
      "end_time": 477563.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the Virgin Mary on the side of a glass window in Sao Paulo."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 477587.0,
      "end_time": 481100.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s when the Virgin Mary made her appearance on a cheese sandwich --"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 481250.0,
      "end_time": 483515.0,
      "text": "which I got to actually hold in a Las Vegas casino --"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 483539.0,
      "end_time": 485750.0,
      "text": "of course, this being America."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 485100.0,
      "end_time": 486625.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 486649.0,
      "end_time": 490976.0,
      "text": "This casino paid $28,500 on eBay for the cheese sandwich."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 491000.0,
      "end_time": 492976.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 493000.0,
      "end_time": 495381.0,
      "text": "But who does it really look like? The Virgin Mary?"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 495405.0,
      "end_time": 497383.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 497408.0,
      "end_time": 501273.0,
      "text": "It has that sort of puckered lips, 1940s-era look."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 501297.0,
      "end_time": 502976.0,
      "text": "Virgin Mary in Clearwater, Florida."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 503000.0,
      "end_time": 504976.0,
      "text": "I actually went to see this one."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 505000.0,
      "end_time": 506834.0,
      "text": "There was a lot of people there."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 506858.0,
      "end_time": 511510.0,
      "text": "The faithful come in their wheelchairs and crutches, and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 511534.0,
      "end_time": 513395.0,
      "text": "We went down and investigated."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 513419.0,
      "end_time": 516592.0,
      "text": "Just to give you a size, that&#39;s Dawkins, me and The Amazing Randi,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 516616.0,
      "end_time": 519290.0,
      "text": "next to this two, two and a half story-sized image."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 519530.0,
      "end_time": 522554.0,
      "text": "All these candles, thousands of candles people had lit in tribute to this."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 522578.0,
      "end_time": 525383.0,
      "text": "So we walked around the backside, to see what was going on."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 525408.0,
      "end_time": 528739.0,
      "text": "It turns out wherever there&#39;s a sprinkler head and a palm tree,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 528763.0,
      "end_time": 529976.0,
      "text": "you get the effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 530000.0,
      "end_time": 533381.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the Virgin Mary on the backside, which they started to wipe off."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 533405.0,
      "end_time": 535976.0,
      "text": "I guess you can only have one miracle per building."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 536000.0,
      "end_time": 539333.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 539357.0,
      "end_time": 543360.0,
      "text": "So is it really a miracle of Mary, or is it a miracle of Marge?"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 543600.0,
      "end_time": 544600.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 544850.0,
      "end_time": 547688.0,
      "text": "And now I&#39;m going to finish up with another example of this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 547712.0,
      "end_time": 550489.0,
      "text": "with auditory illusions."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 550513.0,
      "end_time": 553390.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s this film, \"White Noise,\" with Michael Keaton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 553630.0,
      "end_time": 555597.0,
      "text": "about the dead talking back to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 555621.0,
      "end_time": 559286.0,
      "text": "By the way, the whole business of talking to the dead is not that big a deal."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 559310.0,
      "end_time": 560795.0,
      "text": "Anybody can do it, turns out."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 560819.0,
      "end_time": 563906.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s getting the dead to talk back that&#39;s the really hard part."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 563931.0,
      "end_time": 565290.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 565530.0,
      "end_time": 568835.0,
      "text": "In this case, supposedly, these messages are hidden in electronic phenomena."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 568859.0,
      "end_time": 572144.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a ReverseSpeech.com web page where I downloaded this stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 572168.0,
      "end_time": 575319.0,
      "text": "This is the most famous one of all of these."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 575343.0,
      "end_time": 578144.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the forward version of the very famous song."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 578168.0,
      "end_time": 579239.0,
      "text": "(Music with lyrics)"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 579263.0,
      "end_time": 584421.0,
      "text": "If there&#39;s a bustle in your hedgerow don&#39;t be alarmed now."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 585890.0,
      "end_time": 588884.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just a spring clean for the May Queen."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 590764.0,
      "end_time": 595751.0,
      "text": "Yes, there are two paths you can go by, but in the long run,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 596870.0,
      "end_time": 600434.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s still time to change the road you&#39;re on."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 601514.0,
      "end_time": 603940.0,
      "text": "(Music ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 603733.0,
      "end_time": 606343.0,
      "text": "Couldn&#39;t you just listen to that all day?"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 606368.0,
      "end_time": 607975.0,
      "text": "All right, here it is backwards,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 607999.0,
      "end_time": 612290.0,
      "text": "and see if you can hear the hidden messages that are supposedly in there."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 612513.0,
      "end_time": 619291.0,
      "text": "(Music with unintelligible lyrics)"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 626450.0,
      "end_time": 627744.0,
      "text": "(Lyrics) Satan!"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 627768.0,
      "end_time": 634245.0,
      "text": "(Unintelligible lyrics continue)"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 641934.0,
      "end_time": 643554.0,
      "text": "What did you get? Audience: Satan!"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 643578.0,
      "end_time": 645290.0,
      "text": "Satan. OK, at least we got \"Satan\"."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 645314.0,
      "end_time": 647616.0,
      "text": "Now, I&#39;ll prime the auditory part of your brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 647640.0,
      "end_time": 651770.0,
      "text": "to tell you what you&#39;re supposed to hear, and then hear it again."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 651101.0,
      "end_time": 654902.0,
      "text": "(Music with lyrics)"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 677673.0,
      "end_time": 678759.0,
      "text": "(Music ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 678783.0,
      "end_time": 679990.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 680140.0,
      "end_time": 686403.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 686427.0,
      "end_time": 688976.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t miss it when I tell you what&#39;s there."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 689000.0,
      "end_time": 692250.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 692274.0,
      "end_time": 696309.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to just end with a positive, nice little story."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 696333.0,
      "end_time": 699178.0,
      "text": "The Skeptics is a nonprofit educational organization."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 699202.0,
      "end_time": 702220.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re always looking for little good things that people do."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 702460.0,
      "end_time": 704550.0,
      "text": "And in England, there&#39;s a pop singer."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 704790.0,
      "end_time": 707824.0,
      "text": "One of the top popular singers in England today, Katie Melua."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 707848.0,
      "end_time": 709376.0,
      "text": "And she wrote a beautiful song."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 709400.0,
      "end_time": 714976.0,
      "text": "It was in the top five in 2005, called, \"Nine Million Bicycles in Beijing.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 715000.0,
      "end_time": 718960.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a love story -- she&#39;s sort of the Norah Jones of the UK --"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 718120.0,
      "end_time": 719741.0,
      "text": "about how she much loves her guy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 719765.0,
      "end_time": 722241.0,
      "text": "and compared to nine million bicycles, and so forth."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 722265.0,
      "end_time": 724490.0,
      "text": "And she has this one passage here."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 724514.0,
      "end_time": 725550.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 725574.0,
      "end_time": 731344.0,
      "text": "(Lyrics) We are 12 billion light-years from the edge"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 731369.0,
      "end_time": 733694.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a guess,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 733718.0,
      "end_time": 737429.0,
      "text": "No one can ever say it&#39;s true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 737453.0,
      "end_time": 742550.0,
      "text": "But I know that I will always be with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 742731.0,
      "end_time": 745696.0,
      "text": "Michael Shermer: Well, that&#39;s nice. At least she got it close."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 745720.0,
      "end_time": 748643.0,
      "text": "In America it&#39;d be, \"We&#39;re 6,000 light years from the edge.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 748667.0,
      "end_time": 749703.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 749727.0,
      "end_time": 753496.0,
      "text": "But my friend, Simon Singh, the particle physicist now turned science educator,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 753520.0,
      "end_time": 755646.0,
      "text": "who wrote the book \"The Big Bang,\" and so on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 755671.0,
      "end_time": 758760.0,
      "text": "uses every chance he gets to promote good science."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 758100.0,
      "end_time": 761386.0,
      "text": "And so he wrote an op-ed piece in \"The Guardian\" about Katie&#39;s song,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 761410.0,
      "end_time": 766445.0,
      "text": "in which he said, well, we know exactly how far from the edge."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 766470.0,
      "end_time": 770288.0,
      "text": "You know, it&#39;s 13.7 billion light years, and it&#39;s not a guess."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 770312.0,
      "end_time": 774576.0,
      "text": "We know within precise error bars how close it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 774600.0,
      "end_time": 778410.0,
      "text": "So we can say, although not absolutely true, it&#39;s pretty close to being true."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 778434.0,
      "end_time": 783173.0,
      "text": "And, to his credit, Katie called him up after this op-ed piece came out, and said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 783197.0,
      "end_time": 785568.0,
      "text": "\"I&#39;m so embarrassed. I was in the astronomy club."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 785592.0,
      "end_time": 786870.0,
      "text": "I should&#39;ve known better.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 786894.0,
      "end_time": 788116.0,
      "text": "And she re-cut the song."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 788140.0,
      "end_time": 789988.0,
      "text": "So I will end with the new version."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 790120.0,
      "end_time": 791276.0,
      "text": "(Music with lyrics)"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 791300.0,
      "end_time": 793721.0,
      "text": "We are 13.7 billion light years"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 793745.0,
      "end_time": 797236.0,
      "text": "from the edge of the observable universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 797260.0,
      "end_time": 801290.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a good estimate with well-defined error bars."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 801530.0,
      "end_time": 804205.0,
      "text": "And with the available information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 804229.0,
      "end_time": 808572.0,
      "text": "I predict that I will always be with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 808596.0,
      "end_time": 809753.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 809777.0,
      "end_time": 810945.0,
      "text": "How cool is that?"
